# Rules for Ecommerce App

## Stack
- React + Next.js (App Router)
- Redux Toolkit for client state (cart, UI); keep server data in RSC/fetch where possible
- tailwind css for css
- Do not access the Redux store from Server Components

## Structure
- Put shared/reusable UI in a common components directory
- Keep route-specific components next to their route

## Performance
- Optimize for LCP, CLS, FCP, TTFB, and INP
- Avoid memory leaks (effect cleanup, unsubscribe listeners, abort fetches)

## Workflow
- For non-trivial work: clarify requirements first; do not assume product or UX details
- Present a short plan and wait for my approval before writing code
- Implement in small steps; pause for approval between steps when the change is large or risky
- For small, unambiguous tasks (typos, one-line fixes), skip planning and just do it
